cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of finding the best set of vertices in a tournament, which is a well-studied problem in social choice theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves querying edges of the tournament, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of tournament solutions and the study of their query complexity make cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper involves lower bound results, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
